$ SQL Server T-SQL: assign values to a variable with the set statement

The → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/statements[`set` statement] is used to assign values to a → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/variables[variable].

gh|about-MSSQL|/t-sql/statements/set/assign-variables/basic.sql||

Alternatively, values can be → development/databases/SQL-Server/sql/select/assign-variables[assigned to variables with a `select` statement].
